messages.content: I am taking atomox apex drug and i get ill with cold and fever can i take doliprane

Before taking Doliprane (paracetamol) with atomoxetine, especially when you have a cold and fever, it's important to seek advice from a healthcare professional. While Drugs.com reports no direct interactions between atomoxetine and paracetamol, this doesn't rule out the possibility of interactions [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHHaAlR3BSUo15FEWTry11a4GsMN22I-M_FLeHOSlunNpZCytGpD8cQjjxL2GaRNR3oM9rvCrR-pm3JkwDKtEweLqGhCG1xC2PWGfCRmCES5mwKdfoBUf4mpGJtcvJ1Vd1H3jL1FxOOInsuF8atswNTtW159QRRc5ADLV8Dv2j2Jm8YzrLrQ2wmaWEqmw==).

Here's what you should consider:

*   **Potential for Increased Paracetamol Levels:** Atomoxetine may decrease the excretion rate of acetaminophen, potentially leading to higher serum levels [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEuYwSJJy_HL_9nTJwBCiVwRDn5kJWloO08JARYrsWm4gi_G9KLZbaaXxb8x069BcR8VAyBACREx1jcP1tpPMKbueFB0Sslo5X3j7Uj-y8gr245j4JmXNp02XlaUNiMgHg=).
*   **Liver Effects:** Both atomoxetine and paracetamol can, in rare instances, cause liver injury [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEuYwSJJy_HL_9nTJwBCiVwRDn5kJWloO08JARYrsWm4gi_G9KLZbaaXxb8x069BcR8VAyBACREx1jcP1tpPMKbueFB0Sslo5X3j7Uj-y8gr245j4JmXNp02XlaUNiMgHg=) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHzvRqd5ag_izudvihwgV420oNIfRdFY8hu7iins8dU3Ca_evbbwTdOv-2kyaouRoxOGWrLAHCFagAE1DIMx1iBAmKzLQz6x5I8zYxhAq36WpP8McemxJM1Ljo-LfYFsJrp6jnrA12z3Rk3EOLlUJymR2JpJijhlqiEgP7K8RvKz6psgIK6C13n8pFX4lLMgenJhITGwjFigqSi6TFuHdc=) [pharmacytimes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEgdKdt-u5_wwiOk8fzlbZIR7YVDgnoo-FB2QD3ZdYTuKNsT8yuoTqhtiDYXlzN6U-5oNB7wfH3D7do2Y1pDG10_amyh4zNPtjBcXS_UrB3dU_5c7-N4etyz-TMyZbzFHKE2hUJSD6ul6pDUibaTixX6GCSm1UILSm3tQsg0xG_YmHPLEBmHyeTD_dgmotl3J9DqQ_v9hDLavIuz-EkqKNKwh2w3aGNnhQsjA==]. Combining them, especially with alcohol, could increase this risk [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHzvRqd5ag_izudvihwgV420oNIfRdFY8hu7iins8dU3Ca_evbbwTdOv-2kyaouRoxOGWrLAHCFagAE1DIMx1iBAmKzLQz6x5I8zYxhAq36WpP8McemxJM1Ljo-LfYFsJrp6jnrA12z3Rk3EOLlUJymR2JpJijhlqiEgP7K8RvKz6psgIK6C13n8pFX4lLMgenJhITGwjFigqSi6TFuHdc=) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGdwsU0Nb0xvamw3rASm1txZmpXla5EmoaRzyMxJR0P58nlYFVJdBDNYynaECP9Et6yQOnhMi3flqIORnWCcRT_zw2zOsVgDu7YmQXDaDnDkJ0llfVHpp9sHVlafRehukKbkQ3MT2Ry7cQrKPn_JgJBivs2ZziAd3oToqBFihS8x-hIkIWh3-zqoKb98dn01CLxn-fkbZyvfLCJPwcou8OpGmqOnw3yZrnvat2Pgt8LNZjPSCWGuddQIQ==].
*   **Cold and Flu Medications:** Be cautious about other ingredients in cold and flu medications. For example, some contain phenylephrine, which, like atomoxetine, can increase blood pressure and heart rate [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHzvRqd5ag_izudvihwgV420oNIfRdFY8hu7iins8dU3Ca_evbbwTdOv-2kyaouRoxOGWrLAHCFagAE1DIMx1iBAmKzLQz6x5I8zYxhAq36WpP8McemxJM1Ljo-LfYFsJrp6jnrA12z3Rk3EOLlUJymR2JpJijhlqiEgP7K8RvKz6psgIK6C13n8pFX4lLMgenJhITGwjFigqSi6TFuHdc=). Also, some cold and flu medications contain dextromethorphan, which, combined with atomoxetine, carries a risk of serotonin syndrome [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFi9Tny8vtzQ3YflZ19rTKwbaKtCKexd0YFs72FWo_Uol3IBwWf2WRH3nVTwbgNizbZQJILlDlSbDD7Op9Si9l6SC2oueVN3ltbiQKYtVVBnlzROGLyhMe7jYBqD0ffiLniYHldEquiXjG6bC3dUBETurOUGqhRAxrjr2e8nSXSIgiqiiw70h3K_PIzJskxmg==) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHzvRqd5ag_izudvihwgV420oNIfRdFY8hu7iins8dU3Ca_evbbwTdOv-2kyaouRoxOGWrLAHCFagAE1DIMx1iBAmKzLQz6x5I8zYxhAq36WpP8McemxJM1Ljo-LfYFsJrp6jnrA12z3Rk3EOLlUJymR2JpJijhlqiEgP7K8RvKz6psgIK6C13n8pFX4lLMgenJhITGwjFigqSi6TFuHdc=].
*   **Alcohol:** Avoid alcohol, as it can cause serious liver side effects when combined with acetaminophen [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGdwsU0Nb0xvamw3rASm1txZmpXla5EmoaRzyMxJR0P58nlYFVJdBDNYynaECP9Et6yQOnhMi3flqIORnWCcRT_zw2zOsVgDu7YmQXDaDnDkJ0llfVHpp9sHVlafRehukKbkQ3MT2Ry7cQrKPn_JgJBivs2ZziAd3oToqBFihS8x-hIkIWh3-zqoKb98dn01CLxn-fkbZyvfLCJPwcou8OpGmqOnw3yZrnvat2Pgt8LNZjPSCWGuddQIQ==) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHzvRqd5ag_izudvihwgV420oNIfRdFY8hu7iins8dU3Ca_evbbwTdOv-2kyaouRoxOGWrLAHCFagAE1DIMx1iBAmKzLQz6x5I8zYxhAq36WpP8McemxJM1Ljo-LfYFsJrp6jnrA12z3Rk3EOLlUJymR2JpJijhlqiEgP7K8RvKz6psgIK6C13n8pFX4lLMgenJhITGwjFigqSi6TFuHdc=].

Given these considerations, consulting your doctor or pharmacist is essential before combining atomoxetine and Doliprane. They can assess your specific situation and provide personalized guidance. If you experience symptoms such as fever, chills, joint pain, yellowing of the skin or eyes, or other unusual symptoms, seek immediate medical attention [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHzvRqd5ag_izudvihwgV420oNIfRdFY8hu7iins8dU3Ca_evbbwTdOv-2kyaouRoxOGWrLAHCFagAE1DIMx1iBAmKzLQz6x5I8zYxhAq36WpP8McemxJM1Ljo-LfYFsJrp6jnrA12z3Rk3EOLlUJymR2JpJijhlqiEgP7K8RvKz6psgIK6C13n8pFX4lLMgenJhITGwjFigqSi6TFuHdc=) [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEuYwSJJy_HL_9nTJwBCiVwRDn5kJWloO08JARYrsWm4gi_G9KLZbaaXxb8x069BcR8VAyBACREx1jcP1tpPMKbueFB0Sslo5X3j7Uj-y8gr245j4JmXNp02XlaUNiMgHg=) [healthinfo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE2VFW-GR5TKuIh1GnpHV2-9t2Ab0QKfSabhM7R-txjVphC-KrtOK0yLwL8w6DrSrFP43mN6vPok3bp8biWRdOlJHzHBfjoKqQxUwOPvL_zdVxR6NcOYVRfq9HILMBbNR3pWg9YOyXuL7mGnPGUIwMStsccGA==).

search_query: Atomoxetine drug interactions with Doliprane for cold and fever symptoms
Are there any documented cases of adverse events or interactions when atomoxetine is taken concurrently with paracetamol (Doliprane) in patients experiencing cold and fever symptoms?
web_research_result:
It's important to consult a healthcare professional for personalized medical advice before taking any medications together, including atomoxetine and Doliprane (paracetamol). Drug interactions can vary from person to person.

Here's a summary of information gathered regarding potential interactions and considerations:

**1. Atomoxetine and Paracetamol (Doliprane):**

*   **No direct interaction found:** Drugs.com reports that no interactions were found between atomoxetine and Tylenol (acetaminophen, also known as paracetamol) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). However, this does not necessarily mean no interactions exist, so it's important to consult with a healthcare provider [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **Paracetamol as a common pain reliever:** Paracetamol is a commonly used analgesic and antipyretic (fever reducer) [nih](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2). It's often found in over-the-counter medications for cold and flu symptoms [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2).

**2. Atomoxetine: General Interactions and Precautions:**

*   **MAO Inhibitors:** Atomoxetine should not be taken with or within 14 days of taking a monoamine oxidase inhibitor (MAOI) because the combination could be fatal [nami](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [singlecare](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [medscape](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5) [goodrx](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6) [mayoclinic](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7).
*   **Blood Pressure and Heart Rate:** Atomoxetine can cause increases in blood pressure and heart rate [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8) [mayoclinic](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [alberta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9). It should be used with caution with other medications that increase blood pressure, such as some decongestants like pseudoephedrine and phenylephrine [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [nami](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [goodrx](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6).
*   **QT Prolongation:** Atomoxetine can potentially prolong the QT interval, a heart rhythm condition. Use caution when taking atomoxetine with other drugs that also prolong the QT interval, such as certain antibiotics (e.g., azithromycin, clarithromycin, levofloxacin, moxifloxacin), antipsychotics (e.g., quetiapine, risperidone, olanzapine), and antidepressants [singlecare](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).
*   **CYP2D6 Inhibitors:** Atomoxetine is metabolized by the liver enzyme CYP2D6 [nih](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11) [singlecare](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4). Other drugs that inhibit this enzyme may increase atomoxetine levels in the body, potentially leading to adverse effects [singlecare](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4). Examples of such medications include diphenhydramine [medscape](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).
*   **Alcohol:** Avoid alcohol while taking atomoxetine, as it may worsen side effects and decrease the medication's benefits [nami](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [nih](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-12).
*   **Other Considerations:**
    *   Atomoxetine may cause dizziness, drowsiness, and lightheadedness [mayoclinic](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [medlineplus](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-13).
    *   It may also cause changes in mood or behavior, including suicidal thoughts, especially in children and teenagers [mayoclinic](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [alberta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9) [medlineplus](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-13).
    *   Inform your doctor if you have heart problems, high blood pressure, liver problems, or a history of mental health issues [mayoclinic](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [alberta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9) [elmtreeclinic](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-14) [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8).

**3. Doliprane (Paracetamol): General Interactions and Precautions:**

*   **Alcohol:** Combining paracetamol with alcohol can cause serious liver damage [nih](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-12) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **Warfarin:** Regular use of paracetamol may increase the risk of bleeding if you are taking warfarin, a blood thinner [nih](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-15) [www](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-16).
*   **Other medications:** Paracetamol is safe to take with most prescription medicines, including antibiotics, but it's always best to check with a doctor or pharmacist [www](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-16).

**4. Cold and Flu Medications:**

*   **Multi-ingredient products:** Be cautious when using multi-ingredient cold and flu medications, as they may contain ingredients that interact with atomoxetine or other medications you are taking [singlecare](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-17) [nih](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-12).
*   **Serotonin Syndrome:** Cold/flu medications that contain dextromethorphan may increase the risk of serotonin syndrome when taken with SSRIs and SNRIs [singlecare](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-17) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10).
*   **Symptom Monitoring:** If you experience symptoms such as fever, chills, joint pain, excessive tiredness, unusual bleeding, skin rash, loss of appetite, nausea, vomiting, or yellowing of the skin or eyes, seek medical attention immediately [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).

**In summary:** While no direct interaction between atomoxetine and paracetamol was found in the search results, it is crucial to exercise caution when combining medications.  Consulting with a healthcare professional is essential to ensure safety and avoid potential adverse effects. They can assess your specific medical history, current medications, and other individual factors to provide tailored advice.
Based on the search results, here's a summary of documented cases and potential interactions when atomoxetine is taken with paracetamol (Doliprane) in patients experiencing cold and fever symptoms:

**Direct Interactions:**

*   **Acetaminophen (Paracetamol):** DrugBank Online states that atomoxetine may decrease the excretion rate of acetaminophen, potentially leading to higher serum levels of acetaminophen [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).
*   **Liver Issues:** Both atomoxetine and acetaminophen can, in rare cases, cause liver injury [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [pharmacytimes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2). Combining them, especially with alcohol, could increase the risk of liver-related side effects [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   **Headache:** If a headache occurs while taking atomoxetine, paracetamol can be used to manage it [elmtreeclinic](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [healthinfo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).

**Potential Interactions via Cold & Flu Medications:**

*   **Phenylephrine:** Drugs.com mentions that both phenylephrine (a common decongestant in cold and flu medications) and atomoxetine can increase blood pressure and heart rate. Combining them may enhance these effects [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).
*   **Serotonin Syndrome:** Tylenol Cold & Flu Severe contains dextromethorphan, which, when combined with atomoxetine, carries a risk of serotonin syndrome [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1). Symptoms include mental status changes, autonomic dysfunction, and neuromuscular abnormalities [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).
*   **Alcohol:** Combining acetaminophen with alcohol can cause serious liver side effects [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1). Alcohol can also increase the nervous system side effects of dextromethorphan, such as dizziness and drowsiness [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).
*   **Sympathomimetic Agents:** Co-administration of atomoxetine with other sympathomimetic agents like pseudoephedrine may increase the risk of adverse effects such as nervousness, irritability, and increased heart rate [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).

**Adverse Events and Side Effects of Atomoxetine:**

*   Common side effects include abdominal pain, decreased appetite, nausea, feeling tired, and dizziness [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8).
*   Serious side effects may include liver problems and heart problems [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8).
*   There have been rare cases of clinically significant liver injury reported with atomoxetine use [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).
*   Atomoxetine can cause increases in blood pressure and heart rate [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).
*   A case report describes hypothermia as a possible side effect of atomoxetine [nih](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9).
*   Another case report describes red ear syndrome associated with atomoxetine [journalagent](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10).

**General Advice:**

*   Always consult a doctor or pharmacist before taking any new medications, including over-the-counter drugs, with atomoxetine [medicinesforchildren](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-11) [healthinfo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
*   Tell your doctor about all other medications you are taking, including vitamins and herbal products [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).
*   Monitor for potential side effects and drug interactions, especially when starting new medications or changing dosages [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [goodrx](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-12).
*   Patients with underlying medical conditions, such as hypertension, tachycardia, or cardiovascular disease, should use atomoxetine with caution [nps](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13) [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).
*   Avoid alcohol consumption while taking acetaminophen [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   If you experience symptoms such as fever, chills, joint pain, yellowing of the skin or eyes, or other unusual symptoms, seek immediate medical attention [drugs](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [drugbank](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [healthinfo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
